  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious criminal offense. If caught, potential legal consequences can include:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Federal or state prosecution\n- Potential felony charges\n- Significant prison time (often 5-20 years)\n- Large monetary fines\n\n2. Financial Penalties\n- Seizure of illegally obtained assets\n- Substantial monetary penalties\n- Potential civil asset forfeiture\n\n3. Professional Consequences\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding future employment\n- Professional reputation damage\n\n4. Additional Potential Outcomes\n- Mandatory restitution\n- Probation\n- Supervised release\n- Potential deportation for non-citizens\n\nThe specific penalties depend on factors like:\n- Amount of money laundered\n- Specific circumstances\n- Prior criminal history\n- Jurisdiction\n- Cooperation with authorities\n\nExact consequences vary, but money laundering is treated as a very serious financial crime with significant legal repercussions.",
